			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This spell ROCKS if you have tightly packed mobs and get enough time to cast it.  I hit every mob in the pack for 51 and it doesn't (to my knowledge) hurt the caster like rain of blades if you are too close.  It can make a huge difference in group play when you draw a pack of four, five or six orcs, minotaurs, etc. and have time to stand back and cast it once or twice.  You will draw attention to yourself though, LOL.  Save a bubble of mana to gate.<BR>
<BR>
If you're soloing it's better to use a DD spell IMHO, since you're better off with one dead mob than two half-dead ones.
